        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "Megacystis microcolon intestinal hypoperistalsis syndrome (MMIHS) is a rare congenital disease characterized by massive abdominal distension caused by a largely dilated non-obstructed urinary bladder (megacystis) microcolon and decreased or absent intestinal peristalsis."
        },
